---
import ServiceLayout from '../../../../layouts/ServiceLayout.astro';

const breadcrumbs = [
  { name: 'Home', url: '/' },
  { name: 'Legal Translation', url: '/legal-translation-dubai/' },
  { name: 'Contracts', url: '/legal/contracts/' },
  { name: 'Lease Translation', url: '/legal/contracts/lease/' }
];

const snapshot = [
  { icon: 'key', bold: 'Ejari Ready', text: 'Formatted for Dubai tenancy registration' },
  { icon: 'home', bold: 'Residential & Commercial', text: 'All property types covered' },
  { icon: 'clock', bold: '6-24 Hours', text: 'Standard lease turnaround' },
  { icon: 'gavel', bold: 'RDC Compliant', text: 'Rental Disputes Center accepted' }
];

const processSteps = [
  {
    number: 1,
    title: 'Lease Review',
    text: 'We identify lease type (residential/commercial), special clauses, and any addenda requiring translation.',
    icon: 'file-search'
  },
  {
    number: 2,
    title: 'Legal Translation',
    text: 'MOJ-certified translator handles the document with attention to rent terms, maintenance obligations, and termination conditions.',
    icon: 'file-contract'
  },
  {
    number: 3,
    title: 'Ejari Formatting',
    text: 'Translation formatted to meet Ejari registration requirements, ensuring smooth tenancy contract registration.',
    icon: 'check-circle'
  },
  {
    number: 4,
    title: 'Certified Delivery',
    text: 'MOJ-stamped translation ready for Ejari submission, landlord records, or RDC proceedings.',
    icon: 'certificate'
  }
];

const faqs = [
  {
    question: 'Is Arabic translation required for Ejari registration?',
    answer: 'Ejari accepts both Arabic and English lease contracts. However, if your original lease is in another language (Chinese, French, Hindi, etc.), you will need certified translation into Arabic or English for registration. Arabic translation is also required if you anticipate any disputes that might go to the Rental Disputes Center.'
  },
  {
    question: 'What lease terms require special translation attention?',
    answer: 'Rent payment terms, security deposit conditions, maintenance responsibilities, and early termination clauses are critical. We also pay careful attention to rent increase provisions, subletting restrictions, and any special conditions like pet policies or modification rights.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Do you translate commercial leases?',
    answer: 'Yes. Commercial leases often include additional complexity: fit-out periods, rent-free periods, trading hour requirements, and business-specific restrictions. We understand commercial tenancy terminology and ensure all operational terms are accurately translated.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Can you translate leases for RDC disputes?',
    answer: 'Yes. The Rental Disputes Center requires Arabic documentation. We provide translations formatted for RDC submission, ensuring all relevant clauses are clearly presented for dispute proceedings. We can also translate supporting correspondence and notices.'
  },
  {
    question: 'How quickly can you translate a lease?',
    answer: 'Standard residential leases (5-10 pages) are typically completed within 6-12 hours. Commercial leases with extensive schedules may require 24-48 hours. Rush service is available for urgent Ejari deadlines.'
  }
];

const accordionSections = [
  {
    title: 'Lease Types We Translate',
    id: 'types',
    items: [
      {
        heading: 'Residential Tenancy Contracts',
        body: 'Apartment and villa leases for Ejari registration. Standard terms including rent, security deposit, maintenance responsibilities, and renewal conditions.'
      },
      {
        heading: 'Commercial Leases',
        body: 'Office, retail, and warehouse agreements with business-specific provisions. Fit-out terms, operating hours, and permitted use clauses require specialized translation.'
      },
      {
        heading: 'Short-Term Rentals',
        body: 'Holiday home and serviced apartment agreements. Different regulatory framework with specific DTCM compliance requirements.'
      },
      {
        heading: 'Sublease Agreements',
        body: 'Secondary tenancy arrangements requiring careful translation of primary lease references and subletting permissions.'
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    title: 'Critical Lease Provisions',
    id: 'provisions',
    items: [
      {
        heading: 'Rent & Payment Terms',
        body: 'Payment frequency, accepted methods, late payment penalties, and cheque details. Post-dated cheque requirements are unique to UAE and must be clearly translated.'
      },
      {
        heading: 'Security Deposit',
        body: 'Deposit amount, holding conditions, deduction rights, and return timeline. These terms frequently cause disputes and require precise translation.'
      },
      {
        heading: 'Maintenance Obligations',
        body: 'Landlord vs tenant responsibilities for repairs, AC maintenance, and structural issues. Dubai law has specific default rules that interact with contractual terms.'
      },
      {
        heading: 'Termination Conditions',
        body: 'Notice periods, early termination penalties, and renewal terms. RERA regulations provide certain tenant protections that interact with contractual provisions.'
      },
      {
        heading: 'Eviction Clauses',
        body: 'Grounds for eviction, notice requirements, and procedural steps. Must align with Dubai tenancy law requirements to be enforceable.'
      }
    ]
  }
];
---

<ServiceLayout
  title="Lease Contract Translation Dubai | Tenancy Agreement Translation | Ejari Ready"
  description="MOJ-certified lease translation in Dubai. Residential and commercial tenancy contracts for Ejari registration, RDC disputes. Arabic translation with legal precision."
  keywords="lease translation dubai, tenancy contract translation, ejari translation, rental agreement translation, commercial lease translation dubai"
  heroTitle="Lease Translation"
  heroSubtitle="Tenancy Contracts"
  heroIntro="Whether you're registering a new tenancy with Ejari or preparing for a rental dispute, accurate lease translation protects your rights as tenant or landlord. We translate residential and commercial leases with attention to the specific terms that matter in Dubai's regulated rental market."
  snapshot={snapshot}
  breadcrumbs={breadcrumbs}
  faqs={faqs}
  serviceType="Lease Translation Service"
  processSteps={processSteps}
  processTitle="Our Lease Translation Process"
  accordionSections={accordionSections}
>
  <section class="section bg-light">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Lease Translation for Dubai's Rental Market</h2>
      <p>Dubai's rental market operates under RERA regulations that provide specific tenant and landlord protections. Lease contracts interact with these regulationsâ€”some contractual terms override defaults, while others are unenforceable if they conflict with law.</p>
      
      <p>Our translators understand this regulatory framework. When translating a lease, we ensure that legally significant terms are rendered with precision. A maintenance clause that shifts responsibility to the tenant must be clearly translated to have legal effect. An eviction provision must align with statutory notice requirements.</p>
      
      <p>For dispute situations, translation quality becomes critical. The Rental Disputes Center relies on the Arabic text to understand contractual rights. Ambiguous translation can undermine valid claims or create obligations that weren't intended.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Related Services</h2>
      <div class="related-grid">
        <a href="/legal/contracts/spa/" class="related-card">
          <h3>SPA Translation</h3>
          <p>Property purchase agreements for DLD</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/legal/contracts/" class="related-card">
          <h3>Contract Translation</h3>
          <p>All commercial contract types</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/legal-translation-dubai/" class="related-card">
          <h3>Legal Translation Hub</h3>
          <p>Complete legal document services</p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</ServiceLayout>

<style>
  .related-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }
  
  .related-card {
    padding: 1.5rem;
    background: var(--bg-light, #f8f9fa);
    border-radius: 8px;
    text-decoration: none;
    color: inherit;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--primary-color);
    transition: all 0.2s;
  }
  
  .related-card:hover {
    border-left-color: var(--accent-color);
    background: white;
  }
  
  .related-card h3 {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
    color: var(--primary-color);
  }
  
  .related-card p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin: 0;
  }
</style>
